description:
Continuing through our Lineage Journey, we reach an important point in history where we discover the birth of spiritualism and the state of the dead. In the late 1840's, the Fox sisters founded modern spiritualism. Another key figure to bring the biblical view of the state of man in death was George Storrs. Although he is not as well known, his theological contribution to Adventism was huge as he sought to answer the question - what happens when you die? His answers would go against the grain of popular Christian thought and modern spiritualism which was popularised by the Fox sisters.

To find out more about George Storrs and the Fox Sisters visit our website to read our extended article.
